You write: `I call axioms propositions   From the truth of the axioms it follows that they do not contradict one another.' I found it very interesting to read this very sentence in your letter, for as long as I have been thinking, writing and lecturing on these things, I have been saying the exact reverse: if the arbitrarily given axioms do not contradict one another with all their consequences, then they are true and the things defined by the axioms exist. This is for me the criterion of truth and existence. \\ \hspace*{1ex
